# scripts/guards/check-jsonb-extraction.allowlist
#
# Phase R1 PR-R1-4 — files that query JSONB-bearing tables but lack a
# canonical `*ToResponse` mapper extracting the JSONB column(s).
# Per CLAUDE.md §1.7 incremental adoption — drains as routes migrate
# to the canonical mapper-at-boundary pattern under
# BUG-JSONB-EXTRACTION-MIGRATE-CONSUMERS.
#
# Format: <file>  # comment
#   - <file>     = relative path to the TS file (file-level allowlist;
#                  not line-level since the JSONB check is whole-file)
#   - <comment>  = cascade BUG citation + reason (after #)
# Expiry-policy: per-entry (added 2026-05-03 cycle Phase 0a.7)
# Each non-comment line carries an `| expires: <YYYY-MM-DD> (cascade: <BUG>)`
# OR `| permanent: <reason>` annotation. Entries past their expiry date
# fail the merge gate via `scripts/guards/check-allowlist-expiry.ts`.
# Renewal: when a target close-by date passes, EITHER drain the entry
# (preferred) OR explicitly extend the date with operator authorization.

apps/api/src/features/audit/auditReplayRoutes.ts  # PR-R1-4 baseline tables=audit_log | BUG-JSONB-EXTRACTION-MIGRATE-CONSUMERS — pre-existing JSONB-bearing-table query without canonical mapper per CLAUDE.md §1.7 | expires: 2026-12-31 (cascade: BUG-JSONB-EXTRACTION-MIGRATE-CONSUMERS)
